The Saturday lecture filled with information about character types was seasoned by three visitors from the industry:
by stylist Jan Pokorný, fashion designer Jakub Polanka and fashion photographer Ben Renč.
Jakub reminded us that fashion is illusion and that a stylist should be able to exploit it.
And mailed stylist can work with a single piece of clothing in quite different ways.
The magic word is variability.
For example, you can wear a trench coat over the jeans as usual, like a t-shirt or coat, but you can also wear it on the naked body, put heel shoes on it and wear it as a dress.
It is enough to roll up the sleeves or the collar and the whole look looks very different.
"Play with it," he emphasized.
But the most appropriate advice was: "First, you must know the rules perfectly. "
"Only then can you hurt her," said Jakub.
I finally realize why we need to pauke all these teachings, what we can combine with what and why, even if you often get to see something quite different in fashion journals.
Not to mention fashion shows.
Thanks to the photographer Ben, I now know that a stylist must have prepared much more clothing variants than he ultimately photographed.
So you have to be prepared for a fashion story with ten pages (speak of ten outfits) to style at least fifteen.
And also that the clothing on the photo in combination with other accessories sometimes looks quite different than in reality.
So all of this has to be reckoned with when designing the outfit.
Jan Pokorný also confirmed that image and style sometimes make up half of the success.
You just have to look at Madonna, a not exactly brilliant singer, from whom image and marketing have made a world star.
In the Czech Republic, the services of a stylist are rather reserved.
Also well-known personalities often think this is money thrown out (the main thing is that I bring something as I look at it is secondary).
And if any of us let ourselves be styled, then we should expect that he or she will most likely force us to have a completely different (smaller) size than he or she actually needs.
Then all you have to do is google to find out with certainty that the tabloid press writes, that the corresponding celebrity is back on or off, etc.
On Sunday, Jan and Mario encouraged us not to believe that a stylist only needs to focus on fashion and then "construct" the outfit.
In his work, he has to communicate with the people he styles, and he has to be a smart psychologist.
Evaluate people without bewitching themselves and stand by his opinion.
"If some manager orders us to look at her wardrobe and add some pretty pieces, then we can't clean out the whole wardrobe and tell her - my God, that's terrible."
"You have to find at least a few commendable things to recommend what you can do," says Mario.
He also showed us very concretely what a so-called "place pocket" must contain.
So a bag that you button at the waist and in which you carry with you all the necessary properties.
In addition to such clear things as scissors, strippers to remove hair or safety pins, it also contains such utensils as a nylon thread (this helps the stylist take pictures of products such as handbags or hats), special clips with which the clothing is removed from the back if it is too large (socket needles or other clamps are prohibited so that the fabric does not break) and, of course, sewing stuff.
But in order not only to listen, but also to try something practically, we learned how to stick shoes properly.
Even when photographing in the studio, where the floor is flat, you can damage the sole of the shoe, let alone the outside.
We were glued and glued to o...
