"That's not exactly ideal."
"It doesn't make much sense, however, to hypocritically transfer my shares in the Pilsner Klub to a third person in order to return after one and a half years," Paclík explained.
Pelta promised new statutes of the FAČR, which would lead to a stalemate in the future.
Two days before the general meeting of the football association, one of the candidates for the chairing office, Miroslav Pelta, promised that if he was elected, he would be strongly in favour of the FAČR getting new statutes, which in future exclude disputes about the electoral order from the outset.
