43 percent would discourage acquaintances from such a bank, 49 percent said they were thinking about canceling their account and switching to another institution.
21er Haus in Vienna
The moved pavilion
By Ingeborg Wiensowski
An architectural history with ups, downs and happy ends: The Austrian World Exhibition Pavilion of Brussels won prizes in 1958, became a museum in Vienna, stood empty and decayed.
Now it is reopened as an exhibition house.
If modern post-war architecture is swarmed with clear shapes, glass halls, bold turns and new building materials typical of the belief in technical progress, then the Austrian pavilion of architect Karl Schneider is a fitting and famous example for the Brüssler World Exhibition in 1958.
==History==Schnacker's pavilion was awarded the Grand Prix d'Architecture for its light and floating steel-glass construction.
