But Ospel finally relied on Wuffli.
And Wuffli probably made a decisive mistake in the end: "He thought his models were reality," says Geiger.
"This is a tragic case."
Tragic, maybe.
It's clear: arrogance came before the case.
UBS employees clearly remember the executive meetings on which CEO Wuffli repeatedly made the same statement: Goldman Sachs is coming from the throne.
