So great the euphoria, so deep the case.
One manager after the other had to go as the attempts to clean up were more difficult than thought.
Positions at UBS became a spin-off seat and are still shaky today.
Whoever runs the big bank now has an almost impossible job.
It must find a strategy for a bank that has lost all the obvious business models.
Bank researcher Geiger already has an idea: No more investment banking, focus on asset management, return to Swiss roots.
The bank does not (yet) want to go that far.
But investment banking is supposed to shrink sharply, so much is already clear.
Next Thursday, the new bank manager Sergio Ermotti wants to present his future strategy to the world.
