Fujimori returned to the hospital for medical examination
Former President Alberto Fujimori was admitted to a public hospital on Tuesday to investigate the muscle loss of his legs, informed his family doctor.
The 72-year-old Fujimori, who is 25 years in prison for violation of human rights during his reign (1990-2000), has several illnesses, including tongue cancer, which operates four times and is under control.
Alejandro Aguinaga, Congressman and his personal doctor, told TV that Fujimori would be examined for three days in the Peruvian hospital Instituto Nacional de Enfermedades Neoplásicas to determine the reason for his pain and muscle loss in the lower limbs.
Aguinaga commented that, in his opinion, Fujimori could be pardoned for humanitarian reasons. Nevertheless, he did not wish this because he thought he was innocent.
He was operated four times on tongue cancer and lost 18 kilos of weight. In addition, there are other diseases such as severe erosive gastritis, a cyst in the pancreas, kidney stones, high blood pressure and blood circulation problems in the legs, the doctor counted.
Fujimori has been detained at the Dirección Nacional de Operaciones Especiales de la policía since September 2007.
In April 2009, he was sentenced to 25 years in prison for the murder of 25 people by the death squad of the Peruvian army, which was secretly active during his reign.
Mujica travels to Mexico to strengthen political relations
An official delegation, led by Uruguayan President José Mujica and consisting of several ministers and entrepreneurs, will start their visit to Mexico on Tuesday to expand trade between the two countries and discuss regional policy issues.
Mujica will meet his Mexican counterpart Felipe Calderón next Wednesday. According to the Uruguayan president, this will be the culmination of his booked schedule with politicians, businessmen and a meeting with the Uruguayan collective living in Mexico.
The meeting of both presidents in the city of Guadalajara "suitable for the exchange of information on all policy areas between the two countries," announced the Presidential Office of the South American country on its website.
According to local media, Mujica is looking for Calderón's support for the incident with France when French head of government Nicolas Sarkozy put the South American country on a list of tax havens at the G20 summit in the French city of Cannes.
In his discourse, Sarkozy threatened to exclude those countries that still exist as tax havens from the international community, which was rejected by Uruguay and prompted a request to his ambassador to the European country.
Mexico has been chairing the G20 since November, a group of the most powerful emerging and industrialised countries in the world. Since January of this year, there has been an agreement on the exchange of tax information to avoid double taxation with the South American country.
In recent years, the Government of Uruguay has tried to speed up the practicalisation of tax information exchange agreements in order to be removed from the "grey list" of the Organisation for Economic Cooperation and Development (OECD).
At the business level, there has been a free trade agreement between Mexico and Uruguay since 2004, which has contributed to a growing exchange of goods between the two countries.
The purring installer enters the third dimension with "Super Mario 3D Land"
Super Mario has fought tirelessly for 25 years to save Princess Peach from the clutches of the evil Bowser, but so far never in three dimensions: in "Super Mario 3D Land" he fights for the girl's love in stereo technology.
The game, which comes this month on the counters around the world, was tailored from the beginning to the characteristics of the portable console Nintende 3DS, with which can be played three-dimensionally without a special glasses.
"Mario is the character who has to say how stereoscopy works without glasses," said Omar Álvarez, responsible for the Nintendo press in Spain at the presentation of the video game in Madrid.
Álvarez stated that "Super Mario 3D Land" is "the first video game of Nintendo that has been developed for this console from the very beginning," because so far successful articles such as "Star Fox 64 3D" or "Zelda: Ocarine of time 3D" have been adaptations of existing titles.
Nintendo spokesperson stressed that, although it was three-dimensional, "Super Mario 3D Land" is an "affordable" video game that allows a fast, fluid game.
Álvarez confirmed that "Super Mario 3D Land" contained two games in one: the first part is "light" to capture the less smart users.
After that, the experts can turn a "second round" over the different playing levels, which are becoming increasingly difficult.
In addition, users can choose in real time between an "aggressive D" or one that only affects the depth of the action. However, in order to overcome the obstacles without being victims of the "optical effects," it is always necessary to play three-dimensionally.
This trip Super Marios into the three-dimensional world also means the return of the figure to a portable console, which has not been the case since 2005.
With this video game, Nintendo winks over the fans of the saga and repeats the recipe for success of the last editions: The must-bearded installer has to overcome dangerously-picked platforms to free Princess Peach.
However, the player encounters news about the movements, the environment, the disguises and the enemies - and a "playable" Luigi.
Colom vouches for Portillo's extradition to the United States
The President of Guatemala, Álvaro Colom, announced this Tuesday that he would stand for the extradition of former Governor Alfonso Portillo to be responsible in the United States for the $70 million money laundering plot.
Thus, the trial of the US request for Portillo's extradition ends, so that it can be brought to justice there.
In a press conference, Colom confirmed that his decision was based on the independence of the judiciary and the government, taking into account that a ruling court had already ordered extradition.
He stressed that during his government he had not intervened in court decisions and had accepted all requests for extradition, which he was informed of.
Apart from Portillo, Sergio Ruano Marroquín is being sued for murder and serious assault, Edgar Estrada Morales and Víctor Estrada Paredes, both for drug trafficking.
Colom's action is an act of government that takes place when all judicial and constitutional authorities have exhausted their powers to condemn the former President of the State (2000-2004).
According to the decisions of the Fifth Criminal Court and the Guatemalan Constitutional Court, Portillo must be extradited if its legal situation in Guatemala is clarified and its human rights guaranteed.
Portillo was acquitted for the embezzlement of 120 million Quetzales in the Ministry of Defense during his reign, which was preceded by extradition, but the minister objected and revived the case.
Trinijove has helped 6000 young people threatened by social exclusion
The organisation was set up to prevent the marginalisation of young people without vocational training.
The first 25 years of the social assistance organisation Trinijove have led to important results: in this quarter-century, 6000 young people threatened by social exclusion were supported to find a way out of their difficult situation.
In addition, there are more than one hundred jobs created for this social group.
On the occasion of the anniversary, a review was made yesterday at an event held in Fabra i Coats' former factory buildings, attended by over 300 people.
Trinijove was established in 1986 in the Trinitat Vella district with the aim of helping young people with low levels of education, without work, with drug problems at risk of marginality.
At yesterday's celebration in Sant Andreu, numerous leaders of institutions and institutions who have worked with the association over the past 25 years took part.
The participation of political representatives from different directions during election times proved the impartiality of the work done by Trinijove.
In addition to the President of the Generalitat (Parliament of the Autonomous Region of Catalonia), Artur Mas, and his predecessor Jordi Pujol, the former Socialist Minister of Education Ernest Maragall and the former mayor and currently left-green city council member Ricard Goma took part in the celebrations.
The large hall of Fabra i Coats was also visited by the current Catalan Minister of Social Affairs and Family, Josep Lluís Cleries, and by Jaume Lanaspa, Director-General of the Social Fund of the Savings Bank of La Caixa.
Mas stressed that Trinijove was launched in very difficult times and that today's times are no less complicated, but he added that the work done so far is "a good basis."
For the President of the Generalitat, Trinijove is a model that knows how to fight difficult circumstances and gives hope to people in difficulty.
"The economic crisis is nothing new for the association and the work it does," he explained.
Busy house where huge parties were held was cleared
The house owners had occupied 11 of the 13 apartments in the building on the street Balmes No. 51 (Barcelona).
The twelve squatters left the building yesterday afternoon without any resistance.
All points out that the nightmares of the neighbors of House No. 51 have come to an end on the street Balmes.
Twelve people left the building, which they had illegally occupied yesterday at noon and organized huge festivals that had driven the neighborhood to despair, and were evicted by a court order without police intervention.
After the eviction, the door lock was replaced to avoid a similar situation.
"Access will be checked from now on," confirmed the house manager.
The squatters, who had occupied 11 of the 13 apartments of the building - the rest were inhabited - took the entire electrical system and part of the water supply with them. They had also painted the walls and left behind all kinds of garbage, especially cans with alcoholic beverages.
On the three lower floors huge parties were celebrated, which lasted up to two days and drove the tenants to despair.
Next to the building there is a discotheque, Balmes 51, which also caused damage.
Her owner, Maria Pantinat, told Europa Press that her business had declined by 80% since the beginning of the house occupation.
The owner of the discotheque pointed out that the squatters made their unfair competition because they sold the drinks to three euros, while they cost 10 euros in the discotheque.
In addition, the owner of the resort had been reported by the neighbors because of a disturbance of rest, while according to her statement the noise did not come from the visitors of the disco, but from the squatters and especially from the guests of the festivals that were organized there and which, according to the angry neighbors, have become more and more and longer in recent weeks.
The manager of the discotheque explained that the harassment was so great that she agreed with the owner of the building that she did not have to pay rent for the last nine months.
The Guardia Urbana (urban police) also confirmed that it had received more complaints from its neighbours in recent weeks.
Last week, the president of the PP (Partido Popular - People's Party) in the Barcelona City Council, Alberto Fernández Díaz, demanded that the building be cleared immediately and that the problems of civil coexistence and the coming down of the neighbourhood be dealt with.
He explained that only one floor of the building had been occupied before the summer, but that the squatters had penetrated all the floors of the building and almost all the apartments in the last few months. In some cases even thefts had occurred.
In this sense, he added that "it is necessary to put an end to impunity and to intervene against the antisocial acts in the building."
Yesterday another building in the Nou Barris district was cleared by the Catalan police.
At 3.30 p.m., the police approached Montral No. 35, after receiving a call from a neighbor who had watched four people enter the building.
The four were arrested immediately.
